Coleophora juncivora is a moth of the family Coleophoridae. It is found on Honshu island of Japan.
The wingspan is 9.5–10.5 mm (0.37–0.41 in).The larvae feed on the seeds of Juncus krameri and Juncus leschenaultii. They create a slender, tubular case with a trilobed anal end. It is about 6.5 mm (0.26 in) long, light greyish-ochreous and usually scattered with reddish-grey particles at the basal half.